pokedexEntries.red: The Shellder that is latched onto Slowpoke's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.
pokedexEntries.blue: The Shellder that is latched onto Slowpoke's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.
pokedexEntries.yellow: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.
pokedexEntries.gold: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.
pokedexEntries.silver: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to Shellder's seeping poison.
pokedexEntries.crystal: An attached Shellder won't let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.
pokedexEntries.ruby: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
pokedexEntries.sapphire: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
pokedexEntries.emerald: Its tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This forces it to reluctantly swim and catch prey.
pokedexEntries.fireRed: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
pokedexEntries.leafGreen: The Shellder that latches onto Slowpoke's tail is said to feed on the host's leftover scraps.
pokedexEntries.diamond: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.pearl: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.platinum: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.heartGold: If the tail-biting Shellder is thrown off in a harsh battle, it reverts to being an ordinary Slowpoke.
pokedexEntries.soulSilver: Naturally dull to begin with, it lost its ability to feel pain due to Shellder's seeping poison.
pokedexEntries.black: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.white: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.black2: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.white2: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.
pokedexEntries.x: An attached Shellder won't let go because of the tasty flavor that oozes out of its tail.
pokedexEntries.y: When a Slowpoke went hunting in the sea, its tail was bitten by a Shellder. That made it evolve into Slowbro.
pokedexEntries.omegaRuby: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
pokedexEntries.alphaSapphire: Slowbro's tail has a Shellder firmly attached with a bite. As a result, the tail can't be used for fishing anymore. This causes Slowbro to grudgingly swim and catch prey instead.
pokedexEntries.sun: It spaces out while gazing at the sea. With Shellder's poison flowing through its body, it becomes even spacier.
pokedexEntries.moon: Whenever Shellder bites down hard on its tail, it gives Slowbro a flash of inspiration...which it forgets a moment later.
pokedexEntries.ultraSun: Spacing out is basically all it does. It turns back into Slowpoke if its tail, along with Shellder, breaks off.
pokedexEntries.ultraMoon: Shellder, in its greed to suck out more and more sweetness from Slowbro’s tail, has metamorphosed into a spiral-shaped shell.
